<DATELINE>ALLENTOWN, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 As gingerbread men go, the one at <PERSON> Kinsley </PERSON>'s Market in nearby <LOCATION> Brodheadsville </LOCATION> is very big But at 12 feet tall, it's not big enough for the <ORGANIZATION> Guinness </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Book </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Records </ORGANIZATION>. And if it were big enough, it still would n't make the book because <ORGANIZATION> Guinness </ORGANIZATION> does n't have a category for gingerbread men. `` It's disappointing to us,'' said <PERSON> Kathy </PERSON> <PERSON> Lockwitch </PERSON>, assistant manager at <PERSON> Kinsley </PERSON>'s bakery. `` If we would have known, we would have attempted something else or we would n't have bothered.'' <PERSON> Lockwitch </PERSON> said bakery manager <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Laiso </PERSON> called Guinness before he and <PERSON> Lockwitch </PERSON> made the giant cookie. She says he was told that <ORGANIZATION> Guinness </ORGANIZATION> would consider their claim after they had made their gingerbread man. But <PERSON> Cyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>, assistant editor at <ORGANIZATION> Guinness </ORGANIZATION>, said she told a <PERSON> Kinsley </PERSON> employee that there was no category for a gingerbread man and little chance that <ORGANIZATION> Guinness </ORGANIZATION> would add the category. `` People sometimes do n't want to hear what you're saying,'' she said. `` They do n't want to hear, ` No,' because they're determined to do their thing.'' It took 300 pounds of gingerbread mix, 280 pounds of icing, 600 egg whites and nearly 100 hours to create the giant cookie. `` With all the attention and publicity we got, we thought we were in,'' <PERSON> Lockwitch </PERSON> said. But late last month, <PERSON> Kinsley </PERSON>'s received a letter from Guiness explaining the book's position. Adding insult to injury, the letter added that <PERSON> Kinsley </PERSON>'s had no claim on the world record anyway because a chef in <LOCATION> Buffalo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, created a 24-foot gingerbread man in 1987.
